      "options": {
        "code": {
          "language": "plaintext",
          "showLineNumbers": false,
          "showMiniMap": false
        },
        "content": "# Web Client Overview\n\nweb-client (Next.js) exports OTel traces via `@vercel/otel` (see `web-client/instrumentation.ts`), pushed over OTLP to Tempo like the other services. Unlike the Spring/gen-ai services, web-client has no Prometheus-scrapable metrics endpoint of its own — these RED-style panels instead read `traces_spanmetrics_*`, span metrics that Tempo's metrics-generator derives automatically from the received traces. `span_kind=\"SPAN_KIND_SERVER\"` covers inbound page requests (route rendered = `span_name`); `span_kind=\"SPAN_KIND_CLIENT\"` covers web-client's own outbound fetch calls to api-gateway.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "10.3.3",
      "type": "text"
    },
